headline: Is Costco Stock Still Worth the Premium After Recent Pullback and Slowing Cash Flow Upside?
summary: If you are wondering whether Costco Wholesale is finally on sale or still priced for perfection even after a pullback, you are not alone. The stock has slipped recently, down about 1.3% over the last week and roughly 5.5% over the past month, yet it is still sitting on hefty gains of 94.5% over 3 years and 151.9% over 5 years. Investors have been reacting to a mix of macro headlines around consumer spending resilience and ongoing discussion about the strength of membership-based retail...
